Sarkozy Aide Guaino Says Bank Recapitalizations May Be Necessary

-- B y   H e l e n e   F o u q u e t
-- 
2011-10-06T13:58:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/sarkozy-aide-guaino-says-bank-recapitalizations-may-be-necessary.html
French President Nicolas Sarkozy
adviser Henri Guaino said the government isn’t planning to take
stakes in banks, saying “it isn’t envisaged at the moment.”
Speaking in an interview in Yerevan,  Armenia , he said “maybe a
recapitalization will be necessary” for banks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helene Fouquet in Yerevan, Armenia at 
